OL,3,CTerrence Higgins: One of first people
OL,4,Cin UK to die of AIDs honoured in
OL,5,Chometown
OL,7,FOne of the first people in the UK to
OL,8,Fdie of an AIDs-related illness has
OL,9,Fbeen honoured in his hometown.
OL,11,FTerrence Higgins from Haverfordwest
OL,12,Fdied in 1982, aged just 37. His
OL,13,Ffriends and partner established a
OL,14,Ftrust in his memory.
OL,16,FThe Terrence Higgins Trust remains the
OL,17,Flargest HIV organisation in the UK,
OL,18,Fdelivering services across the nation.
