OL,7,FAccording to accounts detailed by the
OL,8,FTerrence Higgins Trust, Mr Higgins
OL,9,Fsought an official discharge from the
OL,10,Fservice after disclosing his sexuality
OL,11,Fto a senior officer. The response he
OL,12,Fallegedly received was: "If we booted
OL,13,Fout everyone who was gay we wouldn't
OL,14,Fhave a navy left."
OL,16,FHaving been refused discharge, the
OL,17,Fcharity reports he painted red hammer
OL,18,Fand sickle motifs around his ship, and
OL,19,Fwas formally charged and asked to
OL,20,Fleave.
